00:28:32.050 --> 00:28:34.360 align:middle line:84%
So let me talk to you
about this just briefly.

00:28:34.360 --> 00:28:38.200 align:middle line:84%
Compassion is the
end of a sequence.

00:28:38.200 --> 00:28:41.080 align:middle line:90%
A sequence begins with sympathy.

00:28:41.080 --> 00:28:46.660 align:middle line:84%
When we are in sympathy, what
we're saying is that we cannot

00:28:46.660 --> 00:28:48.950 align:middle line:84%
even imagine what
someone is going through.

00:28:48.950 --> 00:28:51.130 align:middle line:84%
But we can sympathize
with their hurt

00:28:51.130 --> 00:28:52.700 align:middle line:90%
or sympathize with their pain.

00:28:52.700 --> 00:28:53.700 align:middle line:90%
You get a sympathy card.

00:28:53.700 --> 00:28:54.370 align:middle line:90%
That's what it says.

00:28:54.370 --> 00:28:56.245 align:middle line:84%
I can only imagine what
you're going through.

00:28:56.245 --> 00:28:57.560 align:middle line:90%
And this is very honest.

00:28:57.560 --> 00:29:00.250 align:middle line:84%
So in sympathy, we
are not experiencing

00:29:00.250 --> 00:29:02.560 align:middle line:84%
the hurt or the pain,
but we're acknowledging

00:29:02.560 --> 00:29:04.347 align:middle line:84%
that hurt her pain
in another person.

00:29:04.347 --> 00:29:05.180 align:middle line:90%
It's the first step.

00:29:05.180 --> 00:29:08.440 align:middle line:84%
The next step from
sympathy is empathy.

00:29:08.440 --> 00:29:12.250 align:middle line:84%
In empathy, we are
actually feeling

00:29:12.250 --> 00:29:14.337 align:middle line:90%
the pain of another person.

00:29:14.337 --> 00:29:15.670 align:middle line:90%
Health care providers know this.

00:29:15.670 --> 00:29:17.860 align:middle line:84%
When you work in an
office as a doctor,

00:29:17.860 --> 00:29:21.280 align:middle line:84%
or a nurse, a practitioner,
a body worker, a massage

00:29:21.280 --> 00:29:26.380 align:middle line:84%
therapist, counselor,
relationship therapist,

00:29:26.380 --> 00:29:28.690 align:middle line:84%
physical therapy,
anything like that,

00:29:28.690 --> 00:29:30.910 align:middle line:84%
you automatically
empathize with the people

00:29:30.910 --> 00:29:33.100 align:middle line:84%
that you're with to
better serve them.

00:29:33.100 --> 00:29:36.280 align:middle line:84%
At the end of the day, if
you've seen 10, 12, 15 people,

00:29:36.280 --> 00:29:38.000 align:middle line:90%
they go home feeling better.

00:29:38.000 --> 00:29:41.620 align:middle line:84%
And if you have not yet learned
how to separate yourself

00:29:41.620 --> 00:29:44.037 align:middle line:84%
from your empathy, you go
home feeling maybe worse thing

00:29:44.037 --> 00:29:46.120 align:middle line:84%
than you did when you came
to work in the morning.

00:29:46.120 --> 00:29:47.662 align:middle line:84%
Because you're
empathizing with them.

00:29:47.662 --> 00:29:49.720 align:middle line:84%
The brain scans
actually show that, when

00:29:49.720 --> 00:29:51.730 align:middle line:84%
we empathize with
someone's pain,

00:29:51.730 --> 00:29:55.030 align:middle line:84%
the pain centers in
the brain of the person

00:29:55.030 --> 00:29:57.790 align:middle line:84%
empathizing light up
in the same places

00:29:57.790 --> 00:30:00.460 align:middle line:84%
but not to the same
degree as they light up

00:30:00.460 --> 00:30:02.590 align:middle line:90%
in the person having the hurt.

00:30:02.590 --> 00:30:03.610 align:middle line:90%
So we experience.

00:30:03.610 --> 00:30:08.740 align:middle line:84%
We say, in empathy, I can
empathize with your pain.

00:30:08.740 --> 00:30:12.110 align:middle line:84%
I am experiencing that pain, the
pain of the loss of a loved one

00:30:12.110 --> 00:30:15.160 align:middle line:84%
or whatever that is-- the
second step to compassion.

00:30:15.160 --> 00:30:17.240 align:middle line:90%
The third step is compassion.

00:30:17.240 --> 00:30:20.380 align:middle line:84%
Compassion is a
step beyond empathy.

00:30:20.380 --> 00:30:23.460 align:middle line:84%
Now I want to talk about
compassion just for a minute

00:30:23.460 --> 00:30:26.800 align:middle line:84%
and define it in a maybe a
little bit different way.

00:30:26.800 --> 00:30:31.630 align:middle line:84%
Compassion is defined as an
emotional experience where we,

00:30:31.630 --> 00:30:35.420 align:middle line:84%
